target: workflows/init
version: 1
validations:
  - name: e2e-oneshot-init-calculator
    type: agent_validation
    severity: error
    args:
      rubric: |
        This is an end-to-end validation that tests the one-shot init workflow
        by generating an intentc project for a web-based calculator using the
        -P flag. All work MUST happen in an isolated temporary directory.

        ## Setup

        1. Create a temporary directory.
        2. `cd` into it.

        ## Run Init

        Run `intentc init calculator -P "A web-based calculator application.
        It should have a clean UI with buttons for digits 0-9, basic arithmetic
        operations (add, subtract, multiply, divide), a display showing the
        current expression and result, and keyboard input support. The frontend
        should be built with HTML/CSS/JavaScript."` from the temporary directory.

        The command should exit with code 0.

        ## Verification

        Verify the generated project structure:

        1. `intent/project.ic` exists, has valid YAML frontmatter with
           `name: calculator`, and its body describes a web-based calculator.
        2. `intent/implementations/default.ic` exists and specifies a web
           frontend stack (HTML/CSS/JavaScript or similar).
        3. At least 3 feature directories exist under `intent/`, each with
           a `.ic` file containing valid YAML frontmatter (`name` and
           `depends_on` fields).
        4. At least one `.icv` validation file exists with valid YAML
           containing a `target` and `validations` list.
        5. The project loads successfully — run `intentc status` from the
           temporary directory and verify it exits with code 0 and lists the
           generated features.
        6. The dependency graph is sensible — foundational features (e.g.,
           core UI, display logic) should not depend on higher-level features
           (e.g., keyboard input).

        ## Cleanup

        Remove the temporary directory when done, regardless of pass/fail.

        ## Pass criteria

        This validation passes if and only if ALL of the above verification
        steps succeed. If any step fails, report which step failed and include
        the relevant command output or error message.
